modules.description: This module provides functions for serializing and deserializing S-expressions, including chaining result values with `let*`, converting values to pretty-printed strings with `to_string_pretty`, and parsing strings into values with `of_string`. It works with S-expressions represented as `Serde.Ser.data` and standard OCaml result types. Concrete use cases include reading and writing configuration files, exchanging structured data in text format, and debugging by printing human-readable representations of complex data.
